2. **Option A: Local Always-On (PM2)**
   
   **Install PM2**
   ```bash
   npm install -g pm2
   ```
   
   **Create ecosystem file**
   ```javascript
   // ecosystem.config.js
   module.exports = {
     apps: [{
       name: "openclaw-gateway",
       script: "openclaw",
       args: "gateway run --port 18789",
       watch: false,
       autorestart: true,
       max_restarts: 10
     }]
   };
   ```
   
   **Start and persist**
   ```bash
   pm2 start ecosystem.config.js
   pm2 save
   pm2 startup  # Auto-start on reboot
   ```
   
   **Monitoring**
   ```bash
   pm2 status
   pm2 logs openclaw-gateway
   pm2 monit
   ```

3. **Option B: Oracle Cloud Free Tier ($0/month)**
   
   **Why Oracle?**
   - 4 OCPU, 24GB RAM - FREE forever
   - More than enough for OpenClaw
   - Tailscale for secure remote access
   
   **Quick Setup**
   ```bash
   # On Oracle VM
   curl -fsSL https://openclaw.ai/install.sh | bash
   
   # Configure for loopback + Tailscale
   openclaw config set gateway.bind loopback
   openclaw config set gateway.auth.mode token
   openclaw doctor --generate-gateway-token
   
   # Install Tailscale
   curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh
   sudo tailscale up --ssh --hostname=openclaw
   
   # Enable as service
   openclaw onboard --install-daemon
   ```
   
   **Access from anywhere**
   ```
   https://openclaw.<your-tailnet>.ts.net/
   ```

4. **Error Recovery**
   
   ```json5
   {
     gateway: {
       health: {
         enabled: true,
         intervalMs: 30000,
         restartOnFail: true
       }
     }
   }
   ```

5. **Monitoring Commands**
   ```bash
   # Health check
   openclaw health
   
   # Status
   openclaw status --all
   
   # Logs
   openclaw logs --follow
   ```

6. **Cost Comparison**
   | Option | Cost | Pros | Cons |
   |--------|------|------|------|
   | Local PM2 | $0 | Simple | Computer must be on |
   | Oracle Free | $0 | Always-on | ARM, setup complexity |
   | DigitalOcean | $6/mo | Easy | Monthly cost |
   | Hetzner | $4/mo | Cheap | EU-focused |

